This paper deals with Bayesian reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) that involves decision making under uncertainty. It also involves the use of policies and exploration strategies, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of bounds and optimization techniques, which are relevant to control systems (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper deals with the calculation of utilities, which is a topic in mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
